gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 124, Pistons 117
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Pistons, 124-117. Anthony Edwards recorded 27 points, five rebounds and eight assists for the Timberwolves, while Karl-Anthony Towns added 27 points (5-5 3PT FG) and six rebounds in the victory. Jaden Ivey tallied a career-high tying 32 points (4-6 3PT FG), along with four rebounds and six assists for the Pistons in the losing effort. The Timberwolves have won three straight games as they improve to 29-11 on the season, while the Pistons fall to 4-37.
